column2: Indicator
column5: dataSource
column8: description

column2: Advanced or proficient reading skills in 3rd grade
column5: School District of Philadelphia
column7: Data are by school year. For example, 2005 refers to the school year spanning fall 2005 and spring 2006.
column8: Percentage of 3rd graders who score at the advanced or proficient levels as assessed by the Pennsylvania System of School Assessment (PSSA) standardized test.

column2: On-time high school graduation
column5: School District of Philadelphia
column7: Data are by school year. For example, 2005 refers to the school year spanning fall 2005 and spring 2006.
column8: Percentage of all students who graduate from high school within four years after starting 9th grade.

column2: Adults completing some college, ≥25 years of age
column5: US Census \ American Community Survey
column8: Percentage of adults 25 years or older who completed at least some college.

column2: Unemployment, ≥16 years of age
column5: Bureau of Labor Statistics
column8: Percentage of population 16 years or older unemployed but seeking work.

column2: Poverty
column5: US Census \ American Community Survey
column8: Percentage of population with an income below 100% of the federal poverty level.

column2: Children living in poverty, <18 years of age
column5: US Census \ American Community Survey
column8: Percentage of children under 18 with a family income below 100% of the federal poverty level.

column2: Children in single-parent households, <18 years of age
column5: US Census \ American Community Survey
column8: Percentage of all children in family households that live in a household headed by a single parent (male or female head of household with no spouse present).

column2: Social capital
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults reporting "yes"to Have people in your neighborhood ever worked together to improve the neighborhood? For example, through a neighborhood watch, creating a community garden, building a community playground, or participating in a block party.

column2: Premature death
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Premature death is represented by the years of potential life lost before age 75 (YPLL-75). YPLL is an age-adjusted rate per 100,000 population.

column2: Life expectancy in years, male
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Life expectancy at birth is the expected number of years to be lived by someone born at the time of calculation, if mortality at each age remains constant in the future.

column2: Life expectancy in years, female
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Life expectancy at birth is the expected number of years to be lived by someone born at the time of calculation, if mortality at each age remains constant in the future.

column2: Poor or fair health
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults who rate their health as fair or poor in response to the question In general, would you say that your health is excellent, very good, good, fair, or poor?

column2: Adult smoking prevalence
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults who have smoked at least 100 cigarettes in their lifetime and currently smoke every day or "some days."

column2: Teen smoking prevalence, 9th-12th grade
column5: Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System
column8: Percentage of 9th-12th grade students who smoked on at least one day in past 30 days.

column2: Smoking-attributable mortality rate per 100,000
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Age-adjusted rate of deaths attributable to smoking per 100,000 adults 35 years and older. This measure is based on CDC's Smoking-Attributable Mortality, Morbidity, and Economic Costs (SAMMEC) methodology at https://apps.nccd.cdc.gov/sammec.

column2: Secondhand smoke exposure at home among children
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of children under 18 who live with an adult who smokes in the home.

column2: Adult excessive drinking
column5: Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System
column8: Also known as “binge drinking”: for women, consuming 4 or more drinks on a single occasion in the last 30 days; for men, consuming 5 or more drinks on a single occasion in the last 30 days.

column2: Teen excessive drinking, 9th-12th grade
column5: Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System
column8: Percentage of 9th-12th grade students who had 5 or more alcoholic drinks in a row within a couple hours on at least one day in past 30 days.

column2: Child obesity prevalence, 5-18 years
column5: School District of Philadelphia
column7: Data are by school year. For example, 2005 refers to the school year spanning fall 2005 and spring 2006.
column8: Percentage of children 5 to 18 years enrolled in the School District of Philadelphia (SDP) with a body mass index (BMI) greater than or equal to the 95th percentile for their age and gender group.

column2: Adult obesity prevalence
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults with BMI greater than or equal to 30kg/m2.

column2: Adults drinking ≥1 sugary drink daily
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults who drank soda, sweetened fruit drinks, and/or bottled teas at least once a day for past 30 days.

column2: Teens drinking ≥1 sugary drink daily, 9th-12th grade
column5: Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System
column8: Percentage of 9th-12th grade students who drank soda at least once a day for past 30 days.

column2: Premature cardiovascular disease (CVD) mortality rate per 100,000
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Age-adjusted rate per 100,000 persons of CVD deaths to persons under 65 years of age.

column2: Adult hypertension prevalence
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults who have been told they have been told by a doctor or other health professional that they have high blood pressure or hypertension. Excludes respondents with a history of gestational hypertension only.

column2: Adult diabetes prevalence
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults who have been told by a doctor or other health professional that they have or have had diabetes. Excludes respondents with a history of gestational diabetes only.

column2: New HIV diagnoses per 100,000
column5: AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Rate of new HIV diagnoses per 100,000 population.

column2: New HIV diagnoses from male-to-male sexual contact
column5: AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from male-to-male sexual contact

column2: New HIV diagnoses from heterosexual contact
column5: AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from heterosexual contact

column2: New HIV diagnoses from injection drug use
column5: AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from injection drug use

column2: New HIV diagnoses from "other" transmission method
column5: AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of new HIV diagnoses from "other" transmission method

column2: Retention in HIV/AIDS care
column5: AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of persons living with diagnosed HIV having had 2 or more CD4 or viral load test results, at least 3 months apart, during a 12 month period.

column2: Viral suppression
column5: AIDS Activities Coordinating Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of persons diagnosed living with HIV, who were alive at year end and had a viral load ≤200 at most recent test. By default, persons without a viral load are classified as not being suppressed.

column2: Adults never tested for HIV, 18-39 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults 18-39 years reporting "never" to the question The next question is about the test for HIV, the virus that causes AIDS. About how long has it been since you last had a test for HIV? Would you say one year or less, more than one year, up to two years, more than 2 years, or never?

column2: Teens who are currently sexually active, 9th-12th grade
column5: Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System
column8: Percentage of 9th-12th grade students who reported having had sexual intercourse during the past 3 months.

column2: Teens who used condom with last sexual encounter, 9th-12th grade
column5: Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System
column8: Percentage of sexually active 9th-12th grade students who reported using a condom during the most recent sexual intercourse. Respondents are considered sexually active if they report intercourse with at least one person in the three months preceding the survey.

column2: Teens who used birth control with last sexual encounter, 9th-12th grade
column5: Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System
column8: Percentage of sexually active 9th-12th grade students who used some form of birth control during the most recent sexual intercourse. Respondents are considered sexually active if they report intercourse with at least one person in the three months preceding the survey.

column2: Teen births per 1,000, 15-19 years of age
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Birth rate per 1,000 teen girls age 15-19 years.

column2: Teen chlamydia rate per 100,000, 15-19 years of age
column5: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Diagnosed chlamydia infection rate per 100,000 teens age 15-19 years.

column2: Teen gonorrhea rate per 100,000, 15-19 years of age
column5: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Diagnosed gonorrhea infection rate per 100,000 teens age 15-19 years.

column2: Infant mortality rate per 1,000 live births
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Mortality rate per 1,000 live-born infants under one year of age.

column2: Low birth weight births
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Percentage of live-born infants weighing less than 2,500 grams or 5 pounds 8 ounces at birth.

column2: Birth parity - 5 or more births
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Percentage of births that are the fifth—or higher order—birth for the mother.

column2: Late or no prenatal care
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Percentage of women who received prenatal care either in the third trimester or not at all, out of all women for whom the timing of prenatal care is known.

column2: Breastfeeding initiation
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Percentage of women initiating breastfeeding before hospital discharge, out of all women for whom breastfeeding status is known.

column2: Children up to date on immunizations, 19-35 months of age
column5: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of children 19-35 months completing recommended vaccination schedule 4:3:1:3 (DTaP : IPV : MMR : Hib).

column2: Asthma hospitalization rate per 100,000 children, <18 years of age
column5: Pennsylvania Health Care Cost Containment Council
column8: Age-adjusted rate of hospital discharges with a primary diagnosis of asthma per 100,000 children under 18.

column2: Elevated blood lead levels in children, 0-5 years of age
column5: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of children 0-5 years with blood lead levels at or above 10 mg/dl.

column2: Pedestrian and bicycle accidents per 100,000 children, <18 years of age
column5: Pennsylvania Department of Transportation
column8: Rate of pedestrian and bicyclist accidents involving motor vehicles per 100,000 children under 18.

column2: Child mortality rate per 100,000, <18 years of age
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Age-adjusted mortality rate per 100,000 children under 18.

column2: Adults without insurance, 18-64 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults 18-64 years reporting no source of insurance.

column2: Children without insurance, <18 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of children under 18 for whom no source of insurance is reported by adult proxy.

column2: Adults covered by Medicaid, 18-64 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults 18-64 years reporting insurance coverage through Medicaid, Medical Assistance (M.A.), HealthChoices, or Access Card.

column2: Adults forgoing care due to cost, 18-64 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults 18-64 years answering "yes" to the question In the past year, has there been any time when you were sick or injured AND did not seek health care because of the cost?

column2: Ambulatory care sensitive hospitalization rate per 100,000
column5: Pennsylvania Health Care Cost Containment Council
column8: Age-adjusted rate per 100,000 persons for conditions where appropriate ambulatory care prevents or reduces the need for admission to the hospital, for population under 75 years of age.

column2: Children with dental visit in past year, 3-17 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of children 3-17 years for whom adult proxy reported dental visit in past 12 months.

column2: Cancer mortality per 100,000
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Age-adjusted rate of cancer deaths per 100,000 persons.

column2: Adults with colonoscopy or sigmoidoscopy in lifetime, 50-74 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults 50-74 years reporting ever having had a colonoscopy or sigmoidoscopy.

column2: Women with mammography in past 2 years, 50-74 years of age
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of women 50-74 years reporting having had a mammogram in the past 2 years.

column2: Girls completing 3-dose HPV vaccine, 13-17 years of age
column5: Division of Disease Control, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of girls 13-17 years who received 3 doses of HPV vaccine out of all girls 13-17 years in the population. Data are based on local reporting of immunizations provided by clinicians, and some underreporting for adolescents may occur.

column2: Food establishments in compliance with food safety regulations upon initial annual inspection
column5: Environmental Health Services, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of food establishments in compliance with food safety regulations upon initial annual inspection by the Philadelphia Department of Public Health.

column2: Rat compliants per 10,000
column5: Environmental Health Services, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Rate of rat complaint calls to the Philadelphia Department of Public Health per 10,000 residents.

column2: Days with good air quality
column5: Air Management Services, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Number of days of the year with Air Quality Index (AQI) levels of 0-50, wherein air quality is considered satisfactory and air pollution poses little or no risk. AQI is a scale from 0 to 500, reflecting measures of ground-level ozone, particulate matter, carbon monoxide, sulfur dioxide, and nitrogen dioxide pose little or no risk. The reporting is based on 2013 Environmental Protection Agency standards.

column2: Violent crime rate per 100,000
column5: FBI Uniform Crime Reports
column8: Rate per 100,000 persons of reported violent crimes, including murders and non-negligent manslaughters, forcible rapes, robberies, and aggravated assaults.

column2: Homicide mortality rate per 100,000
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Age-adjusted rate of homicide deaths per 100,000 persons.

column2: Firearm homicide rate per 100,000, <20 years of age
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Rate of intentional deaths by discharge of firearm per 100,000 persons, presented separately for children and youth under 20 years and adults ≥20 years.

column2: Firearm homicide rate per 100,000, ≥20 years of age
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Number of intentional deaths by discharge of firearm, presented separately for children and youth under 20 years and adults ≥20 years.

column2: Suicide mortality rate per 100,000
column5: Vital Statistics for Philadelphia, Pennsylvania Department of Health
column8: Age-adjusted rate of deaths by intentional self-harm per 100,000 persons.

column2: Teens considering suicide in past year, 9th-12th grade
column5: Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System
column8: Percentage of 9th-12th grade students who seriously considered attempting suicide in past 12 months.

column2: Adults with diagnosed mental health condition
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults answering "yes" to the question Have you ever been diagnosed with any mental health condition, including clinical depression, anxiety disorder or bipolar disorder?

column2: Opioid-related deaths
column5: Medical Examiner's Office, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Number of deaths that were determined by the medical examiner to be caused by drug/medication overdose and for which a toxicology test was positive for an opioid. The medical examiner cannot necessarily determine that it was the opioid that caused the death when there are multiple positive toxicology results, so the term “opioid-related” deaths is used. Opioids include heroin, morphine, methadone, and all prescriptions opioids such as codeine, hydrocodone, and oxycodone. All “intents” of death were included: accident, suicide, homicide, undetermined.

column2: Limited access to healthy foods
column5: Get Healthy Philly, Philadelphia Department of Public Health
column8: Percentage of population with limited access to healthy foods. Time trend and planning district figures reflect analyses of high-poverty areas with low to no walkable access to healthy food as assessed in this report: http://www.phila.gov/health/pdfs/Food_access_report.pdf.

column2: Access to recreational facilities
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column8: Percentage of adults reporting at least monthly use in response to the question In the past year, how often did you use public recreation facilities in your neighborhood, such as public swimming pools, parks, schools, walking trails, bike paths or recreation centers? Response options included "more than once a week," "once a week," "a few times a month," "once a month," "less than once a month," "never."

column2: Access to nearby parks or outdoor space
column5: Public Health Management Corporation (PHMC) Household Health Survey
column7: 2014/15 is the first time period this data was collected.
column8: Percentage of adults reporting they have a nearby park or outdoor space they feel comfortable using.

column2: Pedestrian and bicycle accidents per 100,000
column5: Pennsylvania Department of Transportation
column8: Rate of pedestrian and bicyclist accidents involving motor vehicles per 100,000 persons.
